The Herald Court Reporter Journalist Robert Mukondiwa today appeared at the Harare Magistrates’ Court facing aggravated indecent assault charges following allegations that he sexually attacked an Upper Six student at Allan Wilson High School. The student had visited his apartment in the capital’s Avenues area seeking assistance on how he could reach out to a person staying in the diaspora who had promised to pay him school fees. <img class="size-full wp-image-538367" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/mukondiwa.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/mukondiwa.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/mukondiwa-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Robert Mukondiwa arrives in court with his lawyer Mukondiwa appeared before magistrate Mrs Barbra Mateko who remanded him in custody to April 12. Magistrate Mateko advised Mukondiwa to approach the High Court for bail application. Mr Malvin Mapako prosecuted.